pokedexEntries.red: Its brain can outperform a super-computer. Its intelligence quotient is said to be 5,000.
pokedexEntries.blue: Its brain can outperform a super-computer. Its intelligence quotient is said to be 5,000.
pokedexEntries.yellow: A Pokémon that can memorize anything. It never forgets what it learns—that's why this Pokémon is smart.
pokedexEntries.gold: Closing both its eyes heightens all its other senses. This enables it to use its abilities to their extremes.
pokedexEntries.silver: Its brain cells multiply continually until it dies. As a result, it remembers everything.
pokedexEntries.crystal: It has an IQ of 5000. It calculates many things in order to gain the edge in every battle.
pokedexEntries.ruby: Alakazam's brain continually grows, making its head far too heavy to support with its neck. This Pokémon holds its head up using its psychokinetic power instead.
pokedexEntries.sapphire: Alakazam's brain continually grows, infinitely multiplying brain cells. This amazing brain gives this Pokémon an astoundingly high IQ of 5,000. It has a thorough memory of everything that has occurred in the world.
pokedexEntries.emerald: While it has strong psychic abilities and high intelligence, an Alakazam's muscles are very weak. It uses psychic power to move its body.
pokedexEntries.fireRed: It does not like physical attacks very much. Instead, it freely uses extra-sensory powers to defeat foes.
pokedexEntries.leafGreen: Its brain can outperform a supercomputer. Its IQ (intelligence quotient) is said to be around 5,000.
pokedexEntries.diamond: Its superb memory lets it recall everything it has experienced from birth. Its IQ exceeds 5,000.
pokedexEntries.pearl: Its highly developed brain is on par with a supercomputer. It can use all forms of psychic abilities.
pokedexEntries.platinum: The spoons clutched in its hands are said to have been created by its psychic powers.
pokedexEntries.heartGold: Closing both its eyes heightens all its other senses. This enables it to use its abilities to their extremes.
pokedexEntries.soulSilver: Its brain cells multiply continually until it dies. As a result, it remembers everything.
pokedexEntries.black: The spoons clutched in its hands are said to have been created by its psychic powers.
pokedexEntries.white: The spoons clutched in its hands are said to have been created by its psychic powers.
pokedexEntries.black2: The spoons clutched in its hands are said to have been created by its psychic powers.
pokedexEntries.white2: The spoons clutched in its hands are said to have been created by its psychic powers.
pokedexEntries.x: Its brain cells multiply continually until it dies. As a result, it remembers everything.
pokedexEntries.y: Its brain can outperform a super-computer. Its intelligence quotient is said to be 5,000.
pokedexEntries.omegaRuby: Alakazam's brain continually grows, making its head far too heavy to support with its neck. This Pokémon holds its head up using its psychokinetic power instead.
pokedexEntries.alphaSapphire: Alakazam's brain continually grows, infinitely multiplying brain cells. This amazing brain gives this Pokémon an astoundingly high IQ of 5,000. It has a thorough memory of everything that has occurred in the world.
pokedexEntries.sun: It is said to have an IQ of approximately 5,000. Its overflowing psychokinetic powers cause headaches to anyone nearby.
pokedexEntries.moon: Its brain cells continue to increase in number until its death. The older the Alakazam, the larger its head.
pokedexEntries.ultraSun: Alakazam uses its psychic powers to make the spoons it carries. Each spoon is an original that there’s only one of in the whole world.
pokedexEntries.ultraMoon: If it trusts someone deeply, it will let them have one of its spoons. Anything you eat with that spoon is apparently delicious.
